Problem lies with `Dataset.__setattr__` implementation not passing properties off correctly.

Playing around with trying to automate writing txt files from downloads.  I've got the following line in my personal.ini file:

output_filename: ${author}:${title}${formatext}

but when it writes the file, it keeps the spaces in the title field (and possibly author, but haven't checked yet) so I'd like to try and replace the white space with underscores before the file gets written.

It should be pretty simple, but I couldn't make it work.  I tried to define a new variable called mytitle and then work on replacing this, but I suspect I can't do that:

